snippet.textDisplay:
Indian brothers here are saying Hindi and Urdu are the same because they can understand the song. 😅
Hindi and Urdu are two totally different languages. 
Urdu is a mixture of little Sanskrit, mostly Persian, some Arabic and little Turkish. While Hindi is just Sanskrit in simplified form.
The language Pakistanis and Indians use to communicate is called "Hindustani"  coming from the words "Hindu" and "Pakistani" which is slang and mix of Hindi and Urdu. 
Peace and love to all ❤️
